{"lemma":"مَسْجِدَيْ","slug":"مَسْجِدَيْ","root":"س.ج.د","root_slug":"س-ج-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ج-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَسْجِد","root":"سجد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":28},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18921","n18922"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mosque","examples":[{"text":"مَسْجِد جَامِع","english":"central mosque, great mosque"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the verb سَجَدَ (sajada, “to bow down”). Likely borrowed from a regional Aramaic term for a place of worship, attested in Nabataean Aramaic 𐢓𐢖𐢄𐢅𐢀 (msgdʾ) and in Imperial Aramaic 𐡌𐡎𐡂𐡃𐡀 (msgdʾ) already in the 5th century BCE, the emphatic state of which seems to underlie some of the Romance descendants."},"ipa":["/mas.d͡ʒid/","[mas.d͡ʒɪd]","[mas.ʒɪd]"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18921","headword_ar":"مَسْجَدٌ","root":"sjd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forehead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where is the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1308},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark made by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwad","text_ar":"سُجُوَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostration"},{"kind":"text","text":"in prayer]. (S.) [Said in the TA to be tropical; but not so accord. to the A.] And sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAjidu","text_ar":"مَسَاجِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are the places of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, Mgh, Msb, L;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasaAjidu","text_ar":"المَسَاجِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the forehead, the nose, the hands, the knees, and the feet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the forehead, the hands, and the knees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seven"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=raAb","text_ar":"ا=رَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the forehead, the hands, the knees, and the feet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arb","text_ar":"ارب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) such, accord. to some, is its meaning in the Kur lxxii. 18. (L.) ―         -b2-  See also the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","K","Mgh","L"]},{"entry_id":"n18922","headword_ar":"مَسْجِدٌ","root":"sjd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any place in which one performs the act of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acts of worship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devotion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mosque; a Muslim temple; an oratory;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house in which one performs the act of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IB;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house of prayer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any place in which one performs acts of worship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devotion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) a word of well-known meaning; (K;) sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAjidu","text_ar":"مَسَاجِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, K;) and also pronounced ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masojadN","text_ar":"مَسْجَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) this latter word signifies, accord. to IAar, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAb","text_ar":"مِحْرَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oratory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of private prayer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of prayer of the congregations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any of the parts of the ground, as well as of the body, that are the places of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of the forehead"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the ground in the act of prostration in prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IB.) Fr says, (S,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEl","text_ar":"مَفْعل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of every verb of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"having its aor. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEulu","text_ar":"يَفْعُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with fet-h to the medial radical letter, whether it be a subst, or an inf. n., (S, K,) without any difference, so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala madoxalFA","text_ar":"دَخَلَ مَدْخَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA madoxaluhu","text_ar":"هٰذَا مَدْخَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) except some words (S, K) among substs., (S,) as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masojidN","text_ar":"مَسْجِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToliEN","text_ar":"مَطْلِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoribN","text_ar":"مَغْرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oriqN","text_ar":"مَشْرِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoqiTN","text_ar":"مَسْقِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforiqN","text_ar":"مَفْرِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majozirN","text_ar":"مَجْزِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokinN","text_ar":"مَسْكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marofiqN","text_ar":"مَرْفِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa","text_ar":"رَفَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarofuqu","text_ar":"يَرْفُقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobitN","text_ar":"مَنْبِتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manosikN","text_ar":"مَنْسِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaka","text_ar":"نَسَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanosuku","text_ar":"يَنْسُكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) these being with kesr (S, K) to the medial radical letter (K) as a sign of their being substs.; but sometimes some of the Arabs pronounce it with fet-h in the subst.:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokinN","text_ar":"مَسْكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokanN","text_ar":"مَسْكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have been transmitted; and we have heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almasojidu","text_ar":"المَسْجِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almasojadu","text_ar":"المَسْجَدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaToliEu","text_ar":"المَطْلِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaTolaEu","text_ar":"المَطْلَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and he further says, (S,) fet-h is allowable, (S, K,) in all of these, (S,) even if we have not heard it: but when the verb is of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"having its aor. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEilu","text_ar":"يَفْعِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the n. of place [or time] is with kesr, and the inf. n. is with fet-h, to distinguish the one from the other; so that you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazala manozalFA","text_ar":"نَزَلَ مَنْزَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuzuwlFA","text_ar":"نُزُولًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA manozilupu","text_ar":"هٰذَا مَنْزِلُةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAruhu","text_ar":"دَارُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K. *) ―         -b2-  [Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masojidN jaAmiEN","text_ar":"مَسْجِدٌ جَامِعٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A congregational mosque;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mosque in which a congregation assembles to perform the Friday-prayers."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almasojidu","text_ar":"المَسْجِدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaraAmu","text_ar":"الحَرَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sacred mosque"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Mekkeh]. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hrm","text_ar":"حرم"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almasojidu AlA^aqoSaY","text_ar":"المَسْجِدُ الاَقْصَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The furthest mosque"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is in Jerusalem]. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSw","text_ar":"قصو"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masojidu Alxayofi","text_ar":"مَسْجِدُ الخَيْفِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mosque of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayof","text_ar":"خَيْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] in Minè. (S &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyf","text_ar":"خيف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmasojidaAni","text_ar":"المَسْجِدَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two mosques;"},{"kind":"text","text":"that of Mekkeh and that of El-Medeeneh: (S, Mgh:) so in a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrw","text_ar":"ثرو"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["Zj","S","K","Lth","L","Mgh"]}]}}